{
  "texts": [
    "Mishra et al. (2022) provide a comprehensive study on these methods; unfortunately, 3D applications are rarely mentioned.",
    "Wang et al. (2021b) Fig. 6 Generating objects as voxel grids using 3D-GAE (Guan et al. 2020) expanded the idea of data compression based on autoencoders for 3D using VAEs, to obtain better performance by applying them to point clouds.",
    "Although this method is officially for point clouds, pre-processing and post-processing phases are necessary to voxelize the point clouds, and optionally scale or partition them.",
    "The basic 3D convolutional unit of this method is Voxeption-ResNet (VRN) (Brock et al. 2016).",
    "Nine of these are used for analysis and synthesis transforms, which are then used in the encoder and decoder."
  ]
}